description:
Premium malt beverage. Searching the world. Seeking perfection. Hand crafted. Finest yerba buena mint. New. With real cane sugar. Organic limes & traditional mojito mint. Arguably the most refreshing mojito in the world. Crafted with authentic mojito ingredients you'd find in your local bar in Havana. Organic limes, real cane sugar & traditional mojito mint. At Cayman Jack, it's all about the taste. Cayman Jack searched the world to find the freshest, most natural tasting ingredients. Using only natural cane sugar, organic limes and the traditional mojito mint, used in many bars in Cuba, Cayman Jack's unique mojito recipe has a sophisticated clean finish. So enjoy what is arguably the most refreshing mojito in the world, while Cayman Jack sails off in search of his next amazing cocktail. Flavored ale. Good things come to those who wait - do not drink until you are 21. www.americanvintagebeverage.com. 5.8% alc/vol. Product of USA.

Directions
Craft Knowledge from Cayman Jack: The art of tying the improved clinch knot - the marlin fisherman's stand by. Pass the end of the line through the eye. Wrap it around the standing end about five complete turns. Pass the end back through the loop beside the eye. Then pass the end under the final turn. Tighten the knot and trim the end. Illustrations courtesy of www.animatedknots.com.
